def drop_columns(dataframe):
    dataframe = dataframe.dropna(how='all', axis=1)
    #Distinct variable values
    for col in dataframe.columns:
        if len(dataframe[col].unique()) == 1:
            dataframe.drop(col,inplace=True,axis=1)
    return dataframe.drop_duplicates()

df = drop_columns(df)

Label encoding for categorial variables

In [9]:
def clear_dtype(dataframe):
    for i in df.columns:
        
        try: dataframe[i] = dataframe[i].astype('float')
        except: pass
    
    return dataframe


df = clear_dtype(df)
        

from sklearn import preprocessing

def label_encoding(dataframe):
    enc = preprocessing.LabelEncoder()
    dataframe = dataframe.replace('nan', np.nan)
    for col in dataframe.columns:
        if dataframe[col].dtype == 'object':

            enc.fit(dataframe[col].values.astype('str'))
            dataframe[col] = enc.transform(list(dataframe[col].values.astype('str')))

    return dataframe

df = label_encoding(df)

def drop_unecessary(dataframe):
    
    for col in dataframe.columns:
        
        if '_ref_no' in col or '_id' in col or 'book' in col or '_nbr' in col or 'cls' in col or 'ocif' in col or '_ind' in col or '_cd' in col:
            dataframe = dataframe.drop(col, axis = 1)
    return dataframe

df = drop_unecessary(df)
